### WAVE mode — additional structure

When WAVE mode is detected, author a workflow that wraps the single-ticket engine with the wave loop:

{wave_loop()}

{branch_merge_model()}

{merge_doctrine()}

{escalation_model()}

**Wave workflow structure (author after the SINGLE engine blocks above):**

The wave workflow uses the same phases as SINGLE but wraps them in a wave loop. The integration branch is `wave/<initiative>` (or the user's current branch). Per-ticket branches are `ticket/<slug>`. The Git agent manages worktrees for parallel-eligible tickets. After every merge: Validator (build + test). Escalations accumulate in a list; the final report lists all of them.

---

### Maintenance note

This recipe encodes the current `/implement` + `/code-review` + `/resolve` orchestration shape as of the authoring date (2026-06-12). When those base commands change their orchestration, update this recipe to match. No tooling detects drift — by design (ADR-008 Iron Rule). The reminder lives in the design doc §16.
